<TITLE> Asian Ushu Championship begins April 23 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 19 (bdnews24.com)  The third Asian Ushu Championship, organised by the Bangladesh Ushu Association and sponsored by the Standard Bank Ltd, will get underway on Wednesday at the Suhrawardi Indoor Stadium in Mirpur. India, Sri Lanka, Pakistan, Afghanistan, Nepal and hosts Bangladesh would participate in the three-day meet, SM Shahidul Haque Bhuiyan, secretary of the organising committee, told a press conference at the National Sports Council conference room Saturday. The championship includes two events of Thailu and Sansu for both men's and women's groups. Sponsor Standard Bank will provide Tk 5 lakh out of an estimated budget of Tk 15 lakh while co-sponsors Asian Land Development Ltd and Chinese Embassy will give Tk 4 lakh and Tk 1.5 lakh respectively. Bangladesh Ushu Association president FR Siddiqui and general secretary Didar Hasan Dilu, Standard Bank deputy managing director SA Faruqui were among others present. 
